# Pi2 Suricata Threshold/Suppress Config
# Updated: 2026-04-03
# Purpose: Suppress known-good traffic on eth2 (K3s pod egress)

# === SUPPRESS: Known infrastructure traffic ===

# Tailscale STUN NAT traversal (expected -- Pi2 Tailscale relay)
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2016149
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2016150

# Telegram Bot API (expected -- OpenClaw @frank_is_a_real_bot runs on Pi2)
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2033966
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2033967

# Cloudflare Tunnel (expected -- cloudflared.service for GuardQuote)
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2047122

# === THRESHOLD: Reduce noise from TCP stream analysis ===

# Stream analysis (high volume, low value on monitored egress)
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2210020, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 300
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2210029, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 300
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2210045, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 300
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2210063, type limit, track by_src, count 5, seconds 60

# Protocol edge cases (rate limit)
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2200011, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 600
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2200022, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 600
threshold gen_id 1, sig_id 2260003, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 600
